# Internet Speed Twitter Bot

A Python script that checks your current internet speed using Speedtest.net and tweets at your internet service provider if the speeds are below the promised thresholds.

## Features

- Automatically measures download and upload speeds using Speedtest.net
- Logs into Twitter using your credentials
- Posts a complaint tweet if your internet speeds are below the promised levels
- Uses Selenium for browser automation

## Prerequisites

Before running this script, you'll need:

- Python 3.x installed
- Chrome browser installed
- Twitter account credentials
- Environment variables set for your Twitter email and password

## Installation

1. Clone this repository or download the script
2. Install the required Python packages:
   pip install selenium
3. Download ChromeDriver from https://sites.google.com/chromium.org/driver/ and place it in your PATH or in the same directory as the script
4. Set up environment variables for your Twitter credentials:
export TWITTER_EMAIL="your_twitter_email@example.com"
export TWITTER_PASSWORD="your_twitter_password"

